The paper also discusses constructing agents with bounded optimality for a class of machine architectures in real-time environments, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories. The paper also mentions constructing universal ABO programs, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between bounded optimality and philosophy, economics, and game theory, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category.
